# 5. レッツ、クッキング♪

Toya: ...so I've asked an older student from school to taste test for me. He'll be coming over later today.
Miku: <That's good. Having someone help out should be a shortcut to success.>
Miku: <Anyway, shall we get started?>
Toya: Yes, let's.
Toya: I'd like to follow the procedure described in the recipe as closely as we can. However, when I tried it out yesterday, there were several places where I got stuck...
Toya: If that happens again, Miku, I'd like you to give me some advice.
Miku: <Okay. Then, mind if I have a look at the recipe?>
Toya: Of course, here it is...
Miku: <I see. Very interesting. So this is how you bake cupcakes. >
Miku: <So, how did the ones you made yesterday turn out?>
Toya: Well, when they came out of the oven, they didn't quite rise the way they appeared in the recipe.
Toya: On top of that, when I tasted them, the texture felt like I was eating hard paste.
Miku: <It felt like paste...? Actually, MEIKO did seem to mention something about getting a chiffon cupcake to rise being very important.>
Toya: Yes, I had a feeling...
Miku: <But based on what your testimony... You may not have mixed them properly.>
Toya: I didn't mix them properly?
Miku: <Yes. Apparently, these sorts of sweets rise differently based on how their batter is mixed.>
Miku: <But they may also have trouble rising if you go a bit overboard.>
Toya: I see... I didn't know that...
Toya: Just how much mixing is this going to make me do...?
Toya: Yes, now that you mention it... I did mix the batter for a very long time.
Miku: <Oh, in that case, you can try not mixing it so much this time.>
Miku: <You have a tendency to be too careful or follow instructions too strictly. So, why not mix it only a little bit for this batch?>
Miku: <For example, well... How about two or three times?>
Toya: That little? Are you sure the batter doesn't need to be mixed more?
Miku: <I don't think it's a matter of how many times you mix it. You can still mix it fairly vigorously.>
Toya: I see...
Miku: <Also... You could try using a little more baking powder.>
Miku: <MEIKO told me the other day that it's what helps cakes like these rise.>
Toya: Is that what this powder does...?
Toya: But is it okay for us to put in more than the recipe says...?
Miku: <I think that's up to the individual baker. I mean, everyone puts in different amounts of sugar into their coffee, no?>
Miku: <So, it should be okay to put in a little more baking power if you want them to really rise.>
Toya: Yes, that may be so...
Miku: <Actually, this recipe suggests a few additional options... Do you plan on trying any of these?>
Toya: Yes, I was planning to once I got the hang of baking. I even bought some of those ingredients...
Miku: <Then, let's try putting those in. You may never get to use them if you wait until you “get the hang of things”.>
Toya: But...
Toya: (I am a little worried about going with an alternate option right off the bat... At the same time, I won't learn unless I try.)
Toya: (Plus, I have Miku here to teach me.)
Toya: Okay, then... Let's give it a try.
Toya: So, Miku, please tell me right away if you see me doing something wrong...
Miku: <Okay, I will.>
Rui: Based on the address Aoyagi gave me, his house should be just up ahead...
Rui: (Hehe... I hope his creations are coming along well. I'm looking forward to seeing how they turn out...)
Rui: (Still...)
Tsukasa: Excellent! Thank you, Rui! The menu for our dinner party is all set now!
Rui: You're welcome. I'm glad I could help. I hope Aoyagi enjoys everything.
Tsukasa: Yes, same here!
Rui: Is something wrong...?
Tsukasa: No, I was just reminded of something that happened when we were little...
Tsukasa: The truth is, I never really saw Toya smile all that much back then. He always seemed preoccupied...
Tsukasa: He's changed quite a bit since then, but as an older brother figure, I'd like to see him smile more.
Rui: I see. That explains why you're showing so much concern for him...
Tsukasa: *Nod* That is exactly why!
Tsukasa: So, I'd like to prepare a party for him with such spectacular dishes that he won't have any choice but to enjoy himself!
Rui: (It's interesting how Tsukasa and Aoyagi are trying to do so much for each other.)
Rui: (Still, this is their show... There isn't much that I can do for them...)
Rui: (But I hope things go well for them...)
Rui: Ah, this must be his condo...
Toya: Kamishiro, hello. Thank you for coming over today.
Rui: Yes, thank you for inviting me. Hehe... There's a sweet aroma in the air.
Toya: Oh, yes... They should be ready soon.
Toya: Let me get you something to drink. Please, have a seat.
Rui: Okay, thank you.
Rui: (Now, let's see what he made....)
Miku: <The cupcakes seem just about done. I wonder how it turned out.>
Miku: (Toya had such a serious look on his face... Probably because he wants the recipient of his gift to really enjoy what he made.)
Miku: (I hope they end up being delicious.)
Miku: <Wait, it sounded like the cupcakes just burst...>
Miku: <It must be because they're full of so much energy. I'm sure they're going to be yummy and fun to eat.>
